<recipe>
	<name>Garlic Shrimp</name>
	<notes>This is a pretty good shrimp marinade, reminds one of standard Chinese dishes.</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>3/4-1 lb</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>raw shrimp</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>shelled and de-veined</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>soy sauce</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>peanut oil</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>sherry or whiskey</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2 cloves</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>garlic</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>crushed</preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>Marinate shrimp in other ingredients for an hour or two.  Drain and broil or grill for 4-5 minutes per side.

Variant marinades:  equal parts olive oil and vermouth; white wine and butter with tarragon; olive oil mixed with lemon juice, parsley and garlic.</preparation>
